author: brane
msg: Get the Windows tests running again.
* win-tests.py: Change the way executables are searched for, to account
for the output from the generated project files.

author: brane
msg: Also spracht Zaratusthra in revision 5850 of libsvn_subr/io.c:
(svn_private_config.h):  no need to #include this anymore.
Well, even Zaratusthra can be wrong.
* libsvn_subr/io.c: Include svn_private_config.h again, to give  the
Windows port a chance.

author: brane
msg: Fix a bit more of the Windows dsp generator.  This fixes the entry point
not defined errors for the test files -- I guess the linker didn't know
whether to look for main or WinMain if the subsystem wasn't specifically
set.  It also moves the rest of the stray intermediate build files to
their appropriate location.
Patch by: D.J. Heap <dj@shadyvale.net>
* build/generator/msvc_dsp.ezt:
Add the /subsystem:console option to the linker settings for
.exe files and move some more intermediate build files to
the right location.

author: kfogel
msg: * subversion/libsvn_client/status.c
(add_update_info_to_status_hash): Update this utterly outdated doc
string, in preparation for work on issue #959, making 'svn status'
handle the svn:externals property.

author: kon
msg: * tools/client-side/psvn/psvn.el
(svn-status): Signal an error if DIR is not a directory.
Automatically add the required trailing slash.
Added a related TODO entry, too.
